In this article, President Obama criticizes Republican leaders in the Senate for opposing programs that would create jobs and strengthen the economy. He emphasizes the importance of helping small businesses and extending unemployment benefits for those who lost their jobs during the recession. Obama argues that these measures are not only right for those affected by the recession, but also necessary for the overall recovery. He highlights the obstructionist tactics used by the Republican minority in the Senate to block votes on these issues. The President also addresses the importance of extending unemployment insurance for those struggling to make ends meet and dismisses the notion that it is a form of handout. He urges Congress to pass these measures for the sake of American workers, families, and small businesses. Obama concludes by emphasizing the need to come together and help each other during times of crisis, and expresses confidence in overcoming the challenges and moving towards better days.